<subSubSection id="79B2302D5F098EE85064381A4BEACD4A" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D49051BA68CAFBF3858210CB6A865270" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Local distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1CA050EC81B6508EEBA2341DD7933CF1" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">
In S Siberia, the Leek grasshopper was (and is) distributed very locally. Its populations are usually associated with grass meadow along rivers, but on the Anuy Ouval (near Sychevka settlement) it was found in the meadow steppe with some high grasses, forbs, and bushes (together with 
<taxonomicName id="C8010762034304FEC1D4C4CD2C74C668" genus="M." lsidName="M. aethalinus" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" rank="species" species="aethalinus">
<emphasis id="06F6AF18DBFBB238037B66D0D7C528DB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">M. aethalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2ED5FE4F6EF0CF9B9A000A66CA25C5BF" genus="G." lsidName="G. rufus" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis id="3BD56C733E936FFB63B34EC367B304F4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. rufus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
